videoSnippet.title: Earth vs Space || 50th Anniversary Chess Game || Karjakin vs Cosmonauts
videoSnippet.description:

Anatoli Ivaninshin and Ivan Vagner vs Sergey Karjakin
Karjakin vs. Cosmonauts | Earth vs. Space 50th anniversary chess game, 9.6.2020.
Ruy Lopez, exchange variation, 5.O-O (C69)

1. e4 e5 2. ♘f3 ♘c6 3. ♗b5 a6 4. ♗xc6 dxc6 5. O-O ♗e6 6. b3 c5 7. ♘xe5 ♕d4 8. ♘c4 ♗xc4 9. bxc4 ♕xa1 10. ♘c3 b5 11. ♕h5 ♘f6 12. ♕f3 b4 13. e5 O-O-O 14. ♗a3 ♕xf1+ 15. ♔xf1 bxc3 16. exf6 cxd2 17. ♕a8+ ♔d7 18. ♕d5+ ♔c8 19. ♕a8+ ♔d7 20. ♕d5+ ♔e8 21. ♕e4+ ♔d7

Russian Grandmaster Sergey Karjakin played a game of chess against cosmonauts Anatoly Ivanishin and Ivan Vagner on Tuesday 9th June to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the 1st ever Space-Earth game. The cosmonauts were 400 km above the Earth on the International Space Station, which recently welcomed NASA astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley and their SpaceX spacecraft, while Sergey played from the Moscow Museum of Cosmonautics, exactly 50 years after the first game was played in 1970. The game was organised by the Moscow Museum of Cosmonautics, the Russian space agency Roscosmos and the Russian Chess Federation.
